<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Remember, it is a contract. It only looks like English language.<p>I don't have a full copy of the EULA, but in another article they state that "Work" is "any book or other work you generate using this software". They are talking about the output of the program, they are not restricting your original content.<p>So, if you want to sell a PDF of your book through other channels, you better not make the PDF with this software. Use the "Print to PDF" popup in your regular software or something.</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3496958&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%68%4d%72%48%59%73%37%44%61%62">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=120></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3497061 href="vote?for=3497061&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%68%4d%72%48%59%73%37%44%61%62"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3497061></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=StavrosK">StavrosK</a> 13 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3497061">link</a></span></div><br>
